Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine buff-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (?)
Curator's comments: Name Estieios. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX GAB 1022.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Egypt Exploration Fund (perhaps, rather than an acquisition from Newton)
